track.name: Die For You (with Ariana Grande) - Remix

wiki.summary: Six years after the song’s official release, The Weeknd reunites with the multi-talented Ariana Grande for the official remix of Abel’s 2016 hit “Die for You.” The two had previously collaborated on the “Save Your Tears” remix in 2021, as well as Ariana’s “off the table” in 2020 and “Love Me Harder” in 2014. The remix was later included on Starboy (Deluxe), the deluxe edition of Abel’s third studio album Starboy, on March 14th, 2023. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: Six years after the song’s official release, The Weeknd reunites with the multi-talented Ariana Grande for the official remix of Abel’s 2016 hit “Die for You.” The two had previously collaborated on the “Save Your Tears” remix in 2021, as well as Ariana’s “off the table” in 2020 and “Love Me Harder” in 2014. The remix was later included on Starboy (Deluxe), the deluxe edition of Abel’s third studio album Starboy, on March 14th, 2023. Thanks to TikTok, the original song saw a surge in popularity in early 2023, reaching a new peak on the Billboard Top 100 at #6. This led Ariana to share part of her verse on social media, hinting at a possible collaboration between the two artists. One day later, on February 22, both artists announced their shared remix to the public. Read more on Last.fm.
